blog.name: women-of-sci-fi-and-fantasy
blog.title: Women of Science Fiction & Fantasy
blog.description:
This blog is dedicated to listing the Women of Science Fiction & Fantasy on the Television, the Cinema Screen and in Literature.
I have created this list, as Science Fiction and Fantasy has many fantastic male characters, but the roles that Women play have often seen them in supporting roles or as bit players in a larger story. 
I wanted to recognise all the amazing women who have been a part of the stories, movies and TV programmes that I have enjoyed over the years 
The images in this blog have been chosen to highlight the character, but on occasion, I have had to use photos of the actor.

title: home. (3/12)
body:
Summary: In a world that’s black and white until you meet your soulmate, Theon and Sansa have both seen colors for as long as they can remember. But neither knows who their soulmate is.

Now Theon needs a fake soulmate and Sansa needs a real roommate, so together they agree to put aside their differences - only to discover they’re not very different at all.

iii. white: Despite death, life moves on. 

Sansa glances up at Bran, briefly around the room, before her eyes stay on the unused fireplace. “I can’t stay here.” She turns to Jon and Ygritte. “You don’t mind, do you? It’s just Rickon - ”

“I’m perfectly capable of living by myself - ”

“And I’ll still be close by. It’s just…” Sansa bites her lip, hands twisting in her lap.

“The memories are too much.” Theon didn’t mean to say it out-loud, but the words escape faster than he can think about it, and even when everyone turns to look at him, he stays focused on Sansa. “Too… loud.”

She nods. There’s a moment of hesitation, when it feels like it’s only the two of them in the room, despite literally her entire remaining family sitting there watching. She’s debating saying something, the words stuck on her lips, and he’s just about to absolve her from it when: “You can move into the extra bedroom, if you want.”

Read the rest on AO3.

summary: Have you read Alayne's TWOT chapter? I have a Sansa quote from that chapter that we can cry over: "Please, he doesn't need to...
question: Have you read Alayne's TWOT chapter? I have a Sansa quote from that chapter that we can cry over: "Please, he doesn't need to love me, just make him like me, just a little, that would be enough for now." Are D&D really telling me that this girl will never get to experience romantic love, when the foreshadowing is there even in GRRM's penultimate book?!!!!?? Make it make sense please!!!!
answer:
this has been sitting in my inbox for awhile because every time I read it I get emo….

game of thrones makes no sense to me and I really try to keep the books separate from the show because the books are actually good??? lmao i will not accept sansa never experiencing romantic love ever and i (Hope!!!) grrm wouldn’t do that to our poor girl…maybe he’s writing a huge arc for her. she’s always had hardship with romantic relationship in the show/books so maybe!!!! it’s a build up for a wonderful loving relationship to come??? and sansa will be loved and protected in her home where she belongs?? because it’s what she deserves!!

(also it is grrm so you know that probably won’t happen)
